article.headline: Tulane 82, VMI 74
article.story: NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Taylor Rochestie scored a career-high 22 points, helping Tulane erase a 19-point second-half deficit in an 82-74 victory over VMI on Friday. Tulane (6-5), which trailed 70-59 when VMI's Reggie Williams hit a jumper with 4:39 to go, burst into the lead with an 18-0 run shortly after. Vincent Camper scored five points during the spurt while adding a blocked shot and a steal of an inbounds pass while the Green Wave pressed. Camper's jumper from the foul line with 1:21 remaining gave Tulane a 72-70 lead. Soon after, Rochestie picked off an in-bounds pass and hit one of two free throws, then another Keydet turnover was followed by a Marcus Kinzer's feed to Quincy Davis for a slam dunk, his sixth jam of the game. A missed 3-pointer by VMI (5-4) forced the Keydets to foul Kinzer, who hit both free throws to make it 77-70 with 28.7 seconds remaining. Rochestie, a freshman who scored a career-high 19 points in a victory on Tuesday, shot 8-of-13 in setting his new personal mark on Friday. Davis scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, while Kinzer had 17 points and 10 assists. Williams scored 18 points for VMI, while Matt Coward had 17 points and nine assists and Matt Murrer scored 14 points. In the first half, Tulane was victimized by 11 turnovers as the Keydets built a 44-31 advantage, scoring 14 points off the Green Wave turnovers. <
